  "text": "Carbonyl content assay. The levels of protein carbonyls in the plasma were determined using a spectrophotometric DNPH assay as described previously [CITATION_1] . Briefly, 100 μl of plasma was mixed with 400 μl of buffer solution. After mixing, 500 μl of 30% TCA was added to each tube, vortexed and placed on ice for 10 min. The final precipitate was resolved in 1 ml of 6 mol/l guanidine HCl. The carbonyl contents were calculated from the absorbance measurement at 380 nm using the absorption coefficient of 22,000 mol/cm. The absorbance A 380 was also determined for the sample treated with DNPH and HCl, which was subtracted as a background RT-PCR for antioxidant enzymes. Total RNA was purified from the whole human blood using the RNeasy mini kit (Qiagen), according to the manufacturer's protocol. One microgram of total RNA was reverse transcribed by SuperScript II (Invitrogen), using an oligo-dT primer as described by the manufacturer (Table 1) .",
